<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The 
<taxonomicName authority="Icteromyza" class="Insecta" family="Phytomyzinae" genus="Cerodontha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="(Icteromyza) subsp. subgenus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" species="geniculata" subGenus="Icteromyza" subSpecies="subgenus">subgenus Icteromyza</taxonomicName>
was most recently treated by Boucher, who first revised those species occurring in the north (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4039/n08-033" author="Boucher, S" journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="557 - 562" refId="B12" refString="Boucher, S, 2008. A new species and taxonomic notes on northern Nearctic Cerodontha (Icteromyza) (Diptera: Agromyzidae. The Canadian Entomologist 140 (5): 557 - 562, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4039/n08-033" title="A new species and taxonomic notes on northern Nearctic Cerodontha (Icteromyza) (Diptera: Agromyzidae." url="https://doi.org/10.4039/n08-033" volume="140" year="2008">Boucher 2008</bibRefCitation>
), and then treating the entire Nearctic fauna (Boucher 2012). These studies were preceded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zlobin, VV" journalOrPublisher="An International Journal of Dipterological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="51 - 67" refId="B308" refString="Zlobin, VV, 2000. Review of mining flies of the genus Cerodontha Rondani. IX. Subgenus Icteromyza Hendel (Diptera: Agromyzidae). An International Journal of Dipterological Research 11: 51 - 67" title="Review of mining flies of the genus Cerodontha Rondani. IX. Subgenus Icteromyza Hendel (Diptera: Agromyzidae)." volume="11" year="2000">Zlobin (2000</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zlobin, VV" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Journal of systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="179 - 183" refId="B317" refString="Zlobin, VV, 2007d. Review of mining flies of the genus Cerodontha Rondani, XV. Subgenus Icteromyza Hendel (Diptera, Agromyzidae). Japanese Journal of systematic Entomology 13 (2): 179 - 183" title="Review of mining flies of the genus Cerodontha Rondani, XV. Subgenus Icteromyza Hendel (Diptera, Agromyzidae)." volume="13" year="2007 d">2007d</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Nowakowski, JT" journalOrPublisher="Annales zoologici (Warsaw)" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="67 - 183" refId="B180" refString="Nowakowski, JT, 1962. Introduction to a systematic revision of the family Agromyzidae (Diptera) with some remarks on host plant selection by these flies. Annales zoologici (Warsaw) 20 (8): 67 - 183" title="Introduction to a systematic revision of the family Agromyzidae (Diptera) with some remarks on host plant selection by these flies." volume="20" year="1962">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Nowakowskiâs">Nowakowski's</normalizedToken>
(1962
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nowakowski, JT" journalOrPublisher="Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="633 - 661" refId="B182" refString="Nowakowski, JT, 1967. Vorlaeufige Mitteilung zu einer Monographie der europaeischen Arten der Gattung Cerodontha Rond. (Diptera, Agromyzidae). Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne 37: 633 - 661" title="Vorlaeufige Mitteilung zu einer Monographie der europaeischen Arten der Gattung Cerodontha Rond. (Diptera, Agromyzidae)." volume="37" year="1967">1967</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nowakowski, JT" journalOrPublisher="Annales zoologici, Warszawa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 327" refId="B183" refString="Nowakowski, JT, 1973. Monographie der europaeischen Arten der Gattung Cerodontha Rond. (Diptera, Agromyzidae). Annales zoologici, Warszawa 31 (1): 1 - 327" title="Monographie der europaeischen Arten der Gattung Cerodontha Rond. (Diptera, Agromyzidae)." volume="31" year="1973">1973</bibRefCitation>
) Palaearctic treatments, and of course, 
<bibRefCitation author="Spencer, KA" journalOrPublisher="Agriculture Handbook" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 478" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" refId="B261" refString="Spencer, KA, Steyskal, GC, 1986b. Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. U.S.D.A. Agriculture Handbook 638: 1 - 478, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" title="Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. U. S. D. A." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" volume="638" year="1986 b">
Spencer and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Steyskalâs">Steyskal's</normalizedToken>
(1986b)
</bibRefCitation>
treatment of the fauna of the USA. More than 30 species are known, including 12 in the Nearctic, of which only two occur in the Delmarva states: 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. longipennis" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. longipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Loew) and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. vockerothi" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vockerothi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. vockerothi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Boucher.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
In this subgenus, the antennae are widely separated (but less so than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Hendel, 1920" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1920" class="Insecta" family="Phytomyzinae" genus="Dizygomyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dizygomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Dizygomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the lunule is large, semi-circular, and often bulging, the ocellar triangle extends far anteriorly towards the lunule, and the frons and distal regions of the legs are often yellow, at least in part. Larvae mine in 
<taxonomicName authority="Hendel, 1920" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1920" class="Insecta" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Dizygomyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cyperaceae</taxonomicName>
, the anterior spiracles form long knob-like projections and the hind spiracles are displaced ventrally; puparia have a ventral curve posteriorly (
<bibRefCitation author="Nowakowski, JT" journalOrPublisher="Annales zoologici, Warszawa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 327" refId="B183" refString="Nowakowski, JT, 1973. Monographie der europaeischen Arten der Gattung Cerodontha Rond. (Diptera, Agromyzidae). Annales zoologici, Warszawa 31 (1): 1 - 327" title="Monographie der europaeischen Arten der Gattung Cerodontha Rond. (Diptera, Agromyzidae)." volume="31" year="1973">Nowakowski 1973</bibRefCitation>
; Spencer and Steyakal 1986b; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zlobin, VV" journalOrPublisher="An International Journal of Dipterological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="51 - 67" refId="B308" refString="Zlobin, VV, 2000. Review of mining flies of the genus Cerodontha Rondani. IX. Subgenus Icteromyza Hendel (Diptera: Agromyzidae). An International Journal of Dipterological Research 11: 51 - 67" title="Review of mining flies of the genus Cerodontha Rondani. IX. Subgenus Icteromyza Hendel (Diptera: Agromyzidae)." volume="11" year="2000">Zlobin 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
